chargeHist.descr: Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent

result.execSummary:
The defendant Nathan James Koshak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take/Drive Veh. w/o Consent-Abandon Veh., a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: ***Per the January 18, 2016 correspondence from the District Attorney's Office, the victim has not made a claim for resitution; therefore, restitution is set at $0.
Paid in full - Bond previously posted has been applied.

Defendant to undergo a Psychological Evaluation and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent. Defendant to comply with any counseling or treatment as ordered in the Winnebago County mental health case.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No contact with K. Krentz directly or indirectly. No phone calls, e-mails, text messages, written communications or by third party.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

15CF133 & 15CF134 Cases called @ 3:16 p.m. Defendant Nathan James Koshak in court with attorney Jeanne Zamzow.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Upon motion of the State the Court amends 15CF133 Ct 1 to Take and Drive w/o Consent - Abandon Vehicle contrary to Wis Stat 943.23(3m) and 15CF134 Ct 1 to Criminal Damage to Property contrary to Wis Stat 943.01.  Plea: 15CF133: Ct 1 - NC. 15CF134: Ct 1 - NC.   Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 15CF133: Cts 2 & 3 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Zamzow. Statement by DE. Court orders: S/W 2 yrs probation - Conditions: 15CF134 - Restitution in the amount of $215.28 to be paid to the WC Jail, 15CF133- restitution to K. Krentz held open for a period of 30 days in which time a claim must be submitted and hearing to be held within 60 days, DE to comply with a psychological evaluation and comply with any counseling or treatment the assessment deems appropriate, DE to comply with any counseling or treatment organized through the Winnebago Co Mental Health order, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, NC w/ K. Krentz, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Bond previously posted to be applied after being held for 60 days in the event a further restitution claim is submitted. 15CF134 only - Upon successful completion of probation term, Defendant may petition the Court for expungement pursuant to s. 973.015. No opportunity for expungment in 15CF133. 3 days CFTS in the event of a revocation.

NOT PUT OF RECORD:  15CF-133 and 15CF-134: Attorney Jeanne L. Zamzow in court, appearing in person.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  P/S requested and scheduled.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 14, 2015 at 03:15 pm.
